  "fun_facts": [
    "Known as 'Rochelle salt' after the French city La Rochelle where it was first prepared in 1675",
    "Was the first substance discovered to exhibit piezoelectricity (generates electricity when compressed), leading to its use in early microphones and gramophone pickups",
    "Named after Pierre Seignette, the pharmacist who first synthesized it, hence also called 'Seignette salt'",
    "Less commonly used in food than other tartrate salts, but has important historical significance in electronics"
  ]
